STEP 3: RAMANUJAN BOUND |a_p(f)| <= 2*sqrt(p)
--------------------------------------------------
  Theorem (Deligne 1974, Sem. Bourbaki 355):
  For any eigenform f in S_2(Gamma_0(N)) and p not dividing N,
  |a_p(f)| <= 2*sqrt(p).
  This is a proved theorem, not a conjecture.

  Computational spot-check for N=143 (from M8.1 traces):
  143.2.a.a (dim=1):  max |a_p|/(2*sqrt(p))   = 0.970269 at p=239  < 1 PASS
  143.2.a.b (dim=4):  max |Tr|/(4*2*sqrt(p))  = 0.626391 at p=673  < 1 PASS
  143.2.a.c (dim=6):  max |Tr|/(6*2*sqrt(p))  = 0.432161 at p=509  < 1 PASS
  N=143 Ramanujan computational check: PASS

  N=199, N=311: Ramanujan holds by Deligne (1974).
  No computational data required for a theorem.

