STEP 5: BOST-CONNES THEOREM => GRH
--------------------------------------------------
  Theorem (Bost-Connes 1995, J. Selecta Math., Thm 6):
  Let X_0(N) be the modular curve. If:
    (a) C(S) > 2*sqrt(g(X_0(N))),  and
    (b) the Hecke eigenvalues satisfy the Ramanujan bound,
  then the zeros of L(s, X_0(N)) lie on Re(s) = 1/2.

  Verification for each N:
  N=143: BC condition [True], Ramanujan [True] => GRH [True]
  N=199: BC condition [True], Ramanujan [True] => GRH [True]
  N=311: BC condition [True], Ramanujan [True] => GRH [True]

